        }}></img></a></p>
    <p>{`The Big Buddha (officially called Tian Tan Buddha) was pretty impressive. It is the largest sitting Buddha in Hong Kong, and is quite a destination point for many. The statue is made of bronze and was constructed in 1993. We hiked the steps (which seemed so easy compared to those on the Great Wall), and soon were up in the clouds with Buddha! It was quite a relaxing spot to be, as the clouds swirled around us, we did a walking meditation around Buddha.`}</p>
    <p>{`We then hiked back down the stairs to go get lunch at the monastery, which serves a vegetarian lunch menu. It was pretty tasty too!`}</p>
